## Finding: Solution Spec — go_no_go_gate Skill (References: Loop 1, Loop 4)

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: CRITICAL
### Evidence: Confirmed gap from Loop 1 (no forcing function to synthesize Phase 1 work) and Loop 4 (ideal end-state reverse analysis). No current skill produces a Go/No-Go decision artifact or blocks Phase 2 entry.
### Proposed Resolution:
  - **Skill Name**: `go_no_go_gate`
  - **Phase**: 1 (Brainstorm) — runs LAST in Phase 1 sequence
  - **Trigger Commands**: "go or no-go?", "ready to build?", "phase 1 complete?", "should we proceed?", "using go_no_go_gate skill"
  - **Scope**: This skill aggregates all Phase 1 outputs into a single Decision Brief. It scores the project on 7 weighted dimensions: (1) User Evidence (interview count, finding confidence), (2) Market Size (TAM/SOM sufficient for business model), (3) Competitive Position (clear differentiator identified), (4) Technical Feasibility (no blocking infeasibility), (5) Business Model Viability (unit economics viable), (6) Team Capability (team can execute on spec), (7) Stakeholder Alignment (decision-makers signed off). Score 70+/100 = GO. Score 50-69 = CONDITIONAL GO (list conditions). Score < 50 = NO-GO with explicit reason. Produces a signed Decision Brief document stored in `.agent/docs/1-brainstorm/go-no-go-decision.md`.
  - **Priority**: P0 — Critical. This is the single most impactful missing element.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Blocks Phase 2 entry until minimum evidence threshold met. Prevents the most expensive failure mode: building the wrong thing with full Phase 2-7 investment.
================================================================

## Finding: Solution Spec — assumption_testing Skill (References: Loop 1)

